article.description: — Lester Quinones had 20 points as Memphis beat Tulane 80-74 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Quinones scores 20 to lift Memphis past Tulane 80-74
article.linkText: Quinones scores 20 to lift Memphis past Tulane 80-74
article.story: NEW ORLEANS -- — Lester Quinones had 20 points as Memphis beat Tulane 80-74 on Wednesday night. It was the first American Athletic Conference game of the season for both teams. D.J. Jeffries had 18 points and 11 rebounds for Memphis (5-3). Landers Nolley II added 16 points. DeAndre Williams had 10 points. Gabe Watson had 18 points for the Green Wave (4-1), whose four-game season-opening win streak was snapped. Jordan Walker added 16 points. Jaylen Forbes had 15 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
